   "source": [
    "### Final behavioral dataset:\n",
    "- Each row now represents one account on one trading day, summarized through behavioral features.\n",
    "- This transforms noisy transaction-level data into structured user behavior suitable for anomaly detection."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7cac835c-dc50-4a95-96a8-98e58b716890",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Modeling Approach\n",
    "### 5.1 Problem Framing\n",
    "- We are solving an unsupervised anomaly detection problem.\n",
    "- Each row represents an Account-Day behavioral summary, and the goal is to detect statistical outliers in trading behavior.\n",
    "- There are no labeled targets, so supervised learning is not applicable."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 29,
   "id": "571ded09-9bbc-4e3f-afb6-ec58738b7aee",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# No labels exist in dataset\n",
    "# Therefore we cannot use supervised learning\n",
    "\n",
    "problem_type = \"unsupervised anomaly detection\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5a191c1f-2648-4acc-99a5-7706cb6cac1d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 5.2 Candidate Models\n",
    "- We consider several unsupervised anomaly detection models and select the most suitable one for large-scale tabular behavioral data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "id": "44a7a816-f32b-4c09-8473-6d18bdd9f033",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "models_considered = [\n",
    "    \"Isolation Forest\",\n",
    "    \"Local Outlier Factor (LOF)\",\n",
    "    \"One-Class SVM\",\n",
    "    \"DBSCAN\"\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# LOF: good for local density, poor scalability\n",
    "# One-Class SVM: sensitive to scaling, expensive\n",
    "# DBSCAN: sensitive parameters, poor high-dimensional behavior\n",
    "# Isolation Forest: best tradeoff for scalability + performance"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "657f5f3c-a442-4c8f-88aa-b534547f70c4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 5.3 Final Model Choice: Isolation Forest\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Isolation Forest is selected because it:\n",
    "- works well on high-dimensional tabular data\n",
    "- does not require labeled data\n",
    "- scales efficiently to large datasets\n",
    "- naturally detects rare behavioral patterns"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 31,
   "id": "3484c859-eddf-436e-819a-e3df9d298e1d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.ensemble import IsolationForest\n",
    "\n",
    "model = IsolationForest(\n",
    "    n_estimators=100,\n",
    "    contamination=0.01,\n",
    "    random_state=42\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6fbea93e-43bb-405a-99eb-962128188d01",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 5.4 Feature Space\n",
    "- The model is trained on aggregated Account-Day behavioral features."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "id": "2bc60cc1-47f0-444a-8030-ad5970be3abb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "FEATURE_COLUMNS = [\n",
    "    \"trades_per_day\",\n",
    "    \"total_trade_volume_per_day\",\n",
    "    \"avg_trade_size\",\n",
    "    \"avg_time_between_trades\"\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "X = features_df[FEATURE_COLUMNS].fillna(0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4ccc3aaf-ecbe-4eb0-a7a1-08fc7348839b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 5.5 Feature Scaling\n",
    "- We apply StandardScaler to stabilize feature distributions, especially due to heavy-tailed volume features."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 33,
   "id": "bac77bc3-5ef6-494a-9bac-5e2954d2591c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "\n",
    "X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f3a1b037-6ecd-46d7-aa60-6e9377bdffca",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
