   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 7.3 Feature Deviation Scores\n",
    "- We compute how far each observation deviates from normal behavior using z-score style deviation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 46,
   "id": "a5e6c898-cd6e-4035-b4d3-d2c5d435783f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df_explained = features_df.copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "for col in feature_cols:\n",
    "    mean = baseline_stats[col][\"mean\"]\n",
    "    std = baseline_stats[col][\"std\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "    df_explained[f\"{col}_deviation\"] = (df_explained[col] - mean) / std"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "49741386-1867-4c90-9946-55e9c0c5f6cc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 7.4 Overall Behavioral Deviation Score\n",
    "- We aggregate feature deviations into a single interpretability score."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 47,
   "id": "ba94ba47-f6d9-4068-9689-6a33f5b5c397",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df_explained[\"behavioral_risk_score\"] = (\n",
    "    df_explained[[f\"{c}_deviation\" for c in feature_cols]]\n",
    "    .abs()\n",
    "    .sum(axis=1)\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
